Of the 1,417 initiates who completed their rite of passage at 35 initiation sites throughout the Western Cape, only 10  were hospitalised —  for one day due to dehydration. Zero fatalities were recorded as interventions to ensure safe initiation  paid off. The summer season's initiation rite of passage,  predominantly practised by amaXhosa, amaHlubi and Basotho in the Western Cape, began in November and formally ended on January 31. Among the measures introduced by the province was for parents to take prospective initiates for medical screening at local clinics at least two months before initiation to ensure their physical fitness. Other steps taken included: TimesLIVE